data.dns-servers#DNS Servers:
Each server has a tag, optional type, optional address, and optional detour.
Field Type Required Description tag string yes Unique identifier for this DNS server type string no DNS source type: static (default) or keenetic address string for static IP address of the DNS server, with optional port detour string no Outbound to use when contacting this DNS server The detour field is useful when a DNS server must be reached through a specific connection, usually the same VPN that will carry the matching traffic.
{ "servers": [ { "tag": "vpn_dns", "type": "static", "address": "10.8.0.1", "detour": "vpn" }, { "tag": "google_dns", "address": "8.8.8.8" }, { "tag": "keenetic_dns", "type": "keenetic" } ] }
